# CSS Styling Standards

1. Naming Conventions:
   - Use kebab-case for class names (e.g., `header-navigation`)
   - Component-specific classes should start with the component name (e.g., `header-logo`)
   - Use semantic class names that describe purpose, not appearance

2. Organization:
   - Group related styles together with comments
   - Order properties consistently (layout → box model → typography → visual)
   - Use CSS variables for colors, spacing, and other repeated values

3. Best Practices:
   - Avoid using IDs for styling
   - Minimize nesting to reduce specificity issues
   - Use flexbox and grid for layouts
   - Keep selectors as simple as possible

Example CSS structure:
```css
.component-name {
  /* Layout */
  display: flex;
  justify-content: space-between;
  
  /* Box Model */
  padding: var(--spacing-md);
  margin-bottom: var(--spacing-lg);
  
  /* Typography */
  font-family: var(--font-primary);
  font-size: var(--text-md);
  
  /* Visual */
  background-color: var(--color-background);
  border-radius: var(--border-radius-md);
}
```
